    Scope and Contents
INSTITUTE OF INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS COLLECTION 
Dorothy Dee Longan, wife of John P. Longan, recalls experiences in Guatemala, Brazil, Venezuela, and Thailand as a woman, wife, and mother. She discusses the challenges of each country with regards to: moving, people, climate, culture, language, living conditions, housing, housekeeping, marketing, church, trips, recreation, friends, and sometimes revolutions and terrorism. Also discusses her family background and experiences, Border Patrol work, and the effects of foreign living on children. 38 pp. 
Interview by James D. and Elvera L. Williams, 1984 
Donated by the Oral History Research Office, Columbia University, New York 
